                        <p class="Para">The rationale of authentication has been a topic of study for about a decade and a half. First attempts at formal analysis of authentication protocols were not using logics per se, but were certainly logical. Millenâ€™s <em class="EmphasisTypeItalic ">Interrogator</em> [<span class="CitationRef"><a href="#CR75">Mil84</a></span>, <span class="CitationRef"><a href="#CR65">MCF87]</a></span> was a Prolog based tool specifically designed for authentication protocol analysis that functioned essentially as a special purpose model checker. Kemmerer used the general purpose formal specification language <em class="EmphasisTypeItalic ">Ina Jo</em> and an accompanying symbolic execution tool <em class="EmphasisTypeItalic ">Inatest</em> to specify and analyze protocols [<span class="CitationRef"><a href="#CR59">Kem87</a></span>].</p>
